# Add Dark Mode Toggle and Copy Code Button to Documentation

## Summary

This PR adds two user experience improvements to the Lodash documentation site:
1. **Dark Mode Toggle** - A fixed-position button that allows users to switch between light and dark themes
2. **Copy Code Button** - One-click copy-to-clipboard functionality for all code examples

Both features improve developer experience and accessibility when reading documentation for extended periods.

## Features

### 🌙 Dark Mode Toggle
- Fixed-position button in the top-right corner
- Persists user preference in `localStorage`
- Respects system preference (`prefers-color-scheme`) on first visit
- Smooth transitions between light and dark themes
- Comprehensive dark theme styling for all documentation elements

### 📋 Copy Code Button
- Appears on hover over code blocks
- One-click copy to clipboard using modern Clipboard API
- Fallback support for older browsers
- Visual feedback (checkmark icon) after successful copy
- Accessible with proper ARIA labels
- Works seamlessly in both light and dark modes

## Implementation Details

### New Functions Added

#### 1. `addCopyButtons()` Function

This function adds copy buttons to all code blocks in the documentation:

```javascript
/**
 * Adds copy buttons to code blocks.
 *
 * @private
 * @param {Object} $ The Cheerio object.
 */
function addCopyButtons($) {
  let codeBlockIndex = 0;
  $('.highlight').each(function() {
    const $highlight = $(this);
    const $pre = $highlight.find('pre').first();
    if ($pre.length) {
      codeBlockIndex++;
      const codeId = `code-block-${codeBlockIndex}`;
      $pre.attr('id', codeId);
      
      // Create copy button
      const $copyButton = $('<button>')
        .addClass('copy-code-btn')
        .attr('data-clipboard-target', `#${codeId}`)
        .attr('aria-label', 'Copy code')
        .html('<svg>...</svg>');
      
      // Wrap highlight in a container for positioning
      if (!$highlight.parent().hasClass('code-block-wrapper')) {
        $highlight.wrap('<div class="code-block-wrapper"></div>');
      }
      $highlight.after($copyButton);
    }
  });
}
```

#### 2. `addDarkModeToggle()` Function

This function adds the dark mode toggle button to the page:

```javascript
/**
 * Adds dark mode toggle button and styles.
 *
 * @private
 * @param {Object} $ The Cheerio object.
 */
function addDarkModeToggle($) {
  // Create dark mode toggle button
  const $toggle = $('<button>')
    .addClass('dark-mode-toggle')
    .attr('aria-label', 'Toggle dark mode')
    .attr('title', 'Toggle dark mode')
    .html('<svg>...</svg>');
  
  // Add dark mode toggle button at the beginning of body
  const $body = $('body');
  if ($body.length) {
    $body.prepend($toggle);
  } else {
    // If no body tag, add to the root
    const $root = $('*').first();
    $root.prepend($toggle);
  }
}
```

### Integration into Build Process

Both functions are called during the HTML generation process:

```javascript
// Cleanup highlights.
tidyHighlights($);
// Add copy buttons to code blocks.
addCopyButtons($);
// Add dark mode toggle.
addDarkModeToggle($);
```

### CSS and JavaScript Injection

The build script injects comprehensive CSS styles and JavaScript functionality:

**CSS Features:**
- Dark mode theme colors for backgrounds, text, links, and code blocks
- Fixed positioning for toggle button
- Hover effects for copy buttons
- Smooth transitions and animations
- Responsive design considerations

**JavaScript Features:**
- `localStorage` persistence for theme preference
- System preference detection (`prefers-color-scheme`)
- Clipboard API with fallback support
- Visual feedback for copy operations
- Event handling for both features

### Key Code Snippets

**Dark Mode Toggle JavaScript:**
```javascript
function initDarkMode() {
  const toggle = document.querySelector('.dark-mode-toggle');
  if (!toggle) return;
  
  // Check localStorage for saved preference
  const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem('lodash-theme');
  const prefersDark = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)').matches;
  
  if (savedTheme === 'dark' || (!savedTheme && prefersDark)) {
    document.body.classList.add('dark-mode');
  }
  
  toggle.addEventListener('click', function() {
    document.body.classList.toggle('dark-mode');
    const isDark = document.body.classList.contains('dark-mode');
    localStorage.setItem('lodash-theme', isDark ? 'dark' : 'light');
  });
}
```

**Copy Button JavaScript:**
```javascript
function initCopyButtons() {
  const copyButtons = document.querySelectorAll('.copy-code-btn');
  
  copyButtons.forEach(function(button) {
    button.addEventListener('click', function() {
      const targetId = this.getAttribute('data-clipboard-target');
      const codeBlock = document.querySelector(targetId);
      
      if (!codeBlock) return;
      
      const text = codeBlock.textContent || codeBlock.innerText;
      
      // Use Clipboard API if available
      if (navigator.clipboard && navigator.clipboard.writeText) {
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(function() {
          showCopyFeedback(button);
        }).catch(function(err) {
          fallbackCopyText(text, button);
        });
      } else {
        fallbackCopyText(text, button);
      }
    });
  });
}
```

## Files Changed

- `lib/main/build-site.js` - Added two new functions and integrated them into the build process

## Testing

- ✅ Build script verified - all features present in generated HTML
- ✅ No linting errors
- ✅ Code follows project style guidelines
- ✅ Functions properly documented with JSDoc comments
- ✅ Accessible with proper ARIA labels

## Benefits

1. **Improved Accessibility**: Dark mode reduces eye strain in low-light environments
2. **Better Developer Experience**: One-click code copying saves time and reduces errors
3. **Modern UX**: Features match expectations from other modern documentation sites
4. **No Breaking Changes**: Features are additive and don't affect existing functionality

## Notes

- According to CONTRIBUTING.md guidelines, we don't regenerate `doc/` files - they will be generated when the build runs
- Features will appear on lodash.com/docs after the documentation is rebuilt and deployed
- All CSS and JavaScript is self-contained and injected into the generated HTML

